# AI Study Buddy Feature — Implementation Plan

Add a new "AI Study Buddy" page where students can upload a PDF (lecture notes, textbook chapters, etc.) and ask questions about the document. The Gemini API processes the PDF and answers questions based **only** on the uploaded content.

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Student as Student (Browser)
    participant Frontend as React Frontend
    participant Backend as Express Backend
    participant Gemini as Gemini API

    Student->>Frontend: Upload PDF + type question
    Frontend->>Backend: POST /api/studybuddy/chat (multipart: pdf + question)
    Backend->>Gemini: Send PDF bytes + prompt (Gemini File API)
    Gemini-->>Backend: AI response (grounded in PDF)
    Backend-->>Frontend: JSON { answer }
    Frontend-->>Student: Display answer in chat UI
```

## Key Design Decisions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Client-side simplicity**: The PDF file is sent from the frontend to the backend on each chat request as a multipart upload. The backend forwards the raw PDF bytes to Gemini using its inline data capability. This avoids needing a database table or file-storage layer for uploaded PDFs — keeping the feature self-contained.

> [!NOTE]
> **Gemini model**: We'll use `gemini-2.0-flash` which natively supports PDF file inputs. The PDF is sent as base64-encoded inline data along with the user's question. The system prompt instructs the model to answer **only** from the document content.

